## 🛠️ Step-by-Step: What I Did

---

### ✅ Step 1: Monthly Financial Closing & Management Accounts

- Led the monthly financial closing process ensuring all financial entries were posted accurately and on time
- Performed end-of-month activities:
  - Interest accrual and recognition on loans, investments, deposits, and borrowings using the **Effective Interest Rate (EIR) method**
  - Provision computation — ECL-based impairment provisions as per **IFRS 9**
  - Depreciation and amortization of fixed assets and intangible assets
  - Prepaid and accrued expense adjustments — insurance, rent, subscriptions, etc.
  - Staff cost accruals — salary, bonus, gratuity, leave encashment, PF/SSF contributions
  - Suspense account clearance — ensuring suspense items are investigated and cleared monthly
- Prepared monthly management accounts including:
  - Income Statement
  - Balance Sheet
  - Key financial ratios and highlights
  - Variance commentary against budget
- Presented monthly management accounts to HOD and Senior Management for review

---

### ✅ Step 2: Quarterly Financial Statement Preparation

- Prepared quarterly IFRS/NFRS-compliant financial statements as mandated by NRB and SEBON:
  - Statement of Financial Position
  - Statement of Profit or Loss and Other Comprehensive Income
  - Statement of Changes in Equity
  - Statement of Cash Flows (Indirect Method)
  - Selected Notes to Financial Statements
- Performed all quarterly IFRS adjustments:
  - ECL provision update — re-estimation of PD, LGD, EAD with updated data
  - Fair value measurement of investment portfolio (FVOCI / FVTPL)
  - Deferred tax re-computation based on quarterly temporary differences
  - Actuarial estimate update for employee benefits (gratuity, leave encashment)
- Prepared quarterly financials for website disclosure as required by SEBON Regulations
- Filed quarterly financials with:
  - **NRB** — via SIS Portal and Old Reporting Portal
  - **SEBON** — Securities Board of Nepal
  - **NEPSE** — Nepal Stock Exchange (including notes — "Nots")
- Ensured quarterly financials were consistent with annual accounting policies and presented comparatives

---

### ✅ Step 3: Year-End Financial Closing & Annual Financial Statements

- Led the annual financial closing process — the most intensive and comprehensive closing cycle:
  - Final interest accruals and EIR adjustments for the full year
  - Annual ECL model run — full re-estimation of Expected Credit Loss with year-end data and macroeconomic factors
  - Year-end actuarial valuation for defined benefit obligations (**IAS 19**) — coordinating with external actuaries
  - Final deferred tax computation (**IAS 12**) — comprehensive temporary difference analysis
  - Inventory count and fixed asset verification reconciliation
  - Inter-branch and suspense account reconciliation — full clearance by year-end
  - Related party transaction compilation (**IAS 24**)
  - Contingent liabilities and commitments review (**IAS 37**)
  - Events after reporting period assessment (**IAS 10**)
- Prepared complete annual IFRS/NFRS financial statements with full disclosure notes:
  - Statement of Financial Position
  - Statement of Profit or Loss and Other Comprehensive Income
  - Statement of Changes in Equity
  - Statement of Cash Flows (Indirect Method)
  - **Comprehensive Notes to Financial Statements** covering:
    - Significant accounting policies
    - Financial instrument disclosures (IFRS 7)
    - Risk management disclosures (credit, market, liquidity, operational)
    - Segment reporting
    - Capital adequacy disclosures
    - Related party disclosures
    - Contingencies and commitments
    - Events after reporting date

---

### ✅ Step 4: General Ledger Management & Journal Entry Processing

- Managed the General Ledger (GL) within the Core Banking System
- Posted financial entries including:
  - Routine accounting entries — income, expense, asset, liability
  - IFRS adjustment entries — ECL, EIR, fair value, deferred tax, actuarial
  - Reclassification entries — correcting misclassifications
  - Year-end closing entries — profit transfer, reserve appropriations
- Maintained journal entry documentation with proper narrations, approvals, and supporting documents
- Performed trial balance reviews — checking for unusual balances, unreconciled accounts, and suspense items
- Ensured GL integrity through regular sub-ledger to GL reconciliation:
  - Loan sub-ledger ↔ GL
  - Deposit sub-ledger ↔ GL
  - Fixed asset register ↔ GL
  - Investment register ↔ GL

---

### ✅ Step 5: Financial Statement Quality Review & Cross-Referencing

- Performed rigorous quality assurance review on all financial statements before submission:
  - **Mathematical accuracy** — verifying all totals, sub-totals, and cross-footing
  - **Internal consistency** — ensuring Balance Sheet balances, P&L ties to equity, cash flow reconciles to cash
  - **Cross-referencing** — all note references correctly linked between primary statements and notes
  - **Comparative period accuracy** — prior year figures correctly presented and consistent with prior year published financials
  - **Disclosure completeness** — all IFRS/NFRS required disclosures included
  - **Rounding and formatting** — consistent rounding policy and professional formatting
- Identified and corrected errors before external auditor review, reducing audit adjustments significantly

---

### ✅ Step 6: Annual Book (Annual Report) Preparation

- Prepared the **Annual Book (Annual Report)** — the flagship publication of the bank distributed to shareholders, regulators, and stakeholders
- The Annual Book included:
  - Chairman's Message and CEO's Report
  - Corporate Governance Report — Board composition, committees, meeting attendance
  - Management Discussion & Analysis (MD&A) — business review, financial performance, strategic outlook
  - Directors' Report — statutory disclosures, dividend recommendation, events after reporting date
  - Audited Financial Statements — complete IFRS/NFRS financials with auditor's report
  - Capital Adequacy Disclosures — Basel framework compliance
  - Risk Management Report — credit risk, market risk, liquidity risk, operational risk disclosures
  - Branch Network & Contact Information
  - 5-Year Financial Summary — key financial indicators trend
  - Shareholder Information — shareholding pattern, top shareholders, dividend history
  - Photographs & Visual Content — CSR activities, branch inaugurations, awards
- Coordinated the entire Annual Book production process:
  - Collected inputs from all departments (HR, IT, Credit, Operations, Risk, Compliance)
  - Drafted financial sections and management commentary
  - Coordinated with designers and printers for layout, design, and printing
  - Ensured regulatory compliance of all Annual Book disclosures per NRB and SEBON requirements
  - Final proofreading and sign-off before publication

---

### ✅ Step 7: External Audit Coordination

- Served as the primary liaison between the Finance Department and External Auditors during annual statutory audit
- Activities included:
  - Preparing the **Prepared By Client (PBC) list** — all schedules, workpapers, and supporting documents requested by auditors
  - Responding to audit queries and clarifications in a timely manner
  - Providing audit evidence for all material account balances and transactions
  - Discussing audit adjustments and negotiating treatment where professional judgment was involved
  - Reviewing the draft audit report and auditor's opinion for accuracy of facts
  - Ensuring minimal audit adjustments through proactive quality reviews conducted in Steps 1–5
- Facilitated a smooth and efficient audit process — maintaining professional relationships with audit firms

---

### ✅ Step 8: Financial Posting in Core Banking System

- Posted all financial entries directly into Core Banking Systems (CBS) used by the respective banks:
  - **Pumori** — Lumbini Bikas Bank Ltd
  - **Finacle** — Garima Bikas Bank Ltd
- Managed CBS financial modules including:
  - General Ledger module
  - Fixed Asset module
  - Interest computation module
  - Reporting module
- Ensured proper maker-checker controls were followed for all financial postings
- Generated CBS-based financial reports and reconciled with manually prepared financial statements

---

### ✅ Step 9: Website Financial Publication

- Prepared quarterly and annual financial statements formatted specifically for website publication
- Ensured compliance with:
  - **SEBON Regulation** requiring timely publication of quarterly/annual financials on the bank's official website
  - **NRB Directive** mandating public disclosure of key financial indicators
- Coordinated with the IT/Web team for uploading financial statements to the bank's website within regulatory deadlines
- Verified that published financials on the website matched the filed versions with regulators — ensuring consistency across all publication channels

